{
  "name": "Weapon Grace",
  "_id": "weapongrace00000",
  "type": "skill",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>After long years of practice and extensive training under a master-at-arms, you have learned to be graceful when wielding a certain weapon. When creating your character, choose either Blade, Polearm or Bow. You receive this weapon as a Mastered Weapon. If you already have this chosen category as a Mastered Weapon, you receive a +1 bonus to your Accuracy checks when using a weapon from that category.</p><p><strong>Skill Effect:</strong> Choose Blade/Polearm/Bow; it becomes an additional Mastered Weapon. If chosen category is already a Mastered Weapon, gain +1 bonus to Accuracy checks.</p><p><strong>Usable Circumstances:</strong> -</p><p><strong>Stat Used:</strong> -</p><p><strong>TN:</strong> -</p><section id=\"secret-Dun25FopurqRi9OV\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note.</strong></p><p>This skill has three effects; one for each weapon category. When added to a character, enable the effect of the weapon category you have chosen, and delete the remaining two or leave them disabled. If you gain this same skill again later, enable an additional effect.</p></section>"
    },
    "identifier": "weapon-grace",
    "source": {
      "book": "Ryuutama",
      "custom": ""
    }
  },
